3 SENATE BILL NO. 1594 By: Stanley
4
5
6 An Act relating to teachers; amending 70 O.S. 2021,
Section 6-189, as amended by Section 1, Chapter 92,
7 O.S.L. 2024 (70 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 6-189),
which relates to certification requirements for
8 superintendent and principal; adding requirement for
principal certification to include certain
9 professional education; updating statutory
references; updating statutory language; providing an
10 effective date; and declaring an emergency.
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 6-189, as
15 amended by Section 1, Chapter 92, O.S.L. 2024 (70 O.S. Supp. 2025,
16 Section 6-189), is amended to read as follows:
17 Section 6-189. A. The certification system required by the
18 Oklahoma Teacher Preparation Act as part of the new teacher
19 preparation system shall be competency-based. The competencies for
20 certification shall be integrated with competencies specified in
21 Section 6-185 of this title. By July 1, 1996, the State Board of
22 Education shall adopt general competencies for certification, and by
23 January 1, 1997, the Board shall have adopted full competencies and
24 implemented the certification system as required in this act the
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1594 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 Okla homa Teacher Preparation Act. No higher education courses or
2 credit hours may be specified by the State Board of Education in
3 rules for certification. Nothing in the certification rules adopted
4 by the Board shall prohibit the Oklahoma State Regents for Higher
5 Education from adopting policies and procedures it deems appropriate
6 for coursework, grade point average, or credit hours for teacher
7 preparation at institutions in The Oklahoma State System of Higher
8 Education.
9 B. The certification requirements for a school principal not
10 alternatively certified under subsection D of this section shall
11 include not less than:
12 1. Completion of a standard master’s degree;
13 2. Completion of a program in education administration approved
14 by the Oklahoma Commission for Teacher Preparation Educational
15 Quality and Accountability with an emphasis on curriculum,
16 instruction, and building-level leadership skills. The requirement
17 in this paragraph shall not apply to any person who has completed a
18 master’s degree program in education that included competencies that
19 are substantially equal to those listed in this paragraph and if the
20 degree was completed prior to July 1, 2005;
21 3. a. Any other professional education and requirements as
22 may be fixed by the State Board of Education.
23 b. The requirements of this paragraph shall include
24 professional education specific to the Individuals
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1594 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 with Disabilities Education Act (IDEA) and applicable
2 state laws related to the provision of special
3 education services which shall include at a minimum:
4 (1) federal and state laws and regulations related to
5 the provision of special education services,
6 (2) procedural safeguards and parental rights,
7 (3) child find obligations and evaluation
8 requirements,
9 (4) development, implementation, and monitoring of
10 individualized education programs (IEPs),
11 (5) discipline of students with disabilities, and
12 (6) due process hearings, complaint procedures, and
13 compliance obligations of public school districts
14 and administrators.
15 c. The State Board of Education shall promulgate rules
16 providing for approval of professional education
17 providers and courses, documentation and reporting
18 requirements, and procedures for verifying completion
19 of the required professional education.
20 d. Professional education completed pursuant to this
21 paragraph may be used to satisfy professional
22 development or continuing education requirements for
23 certification renewal;
24
