(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 4. A passing score on the subject area competency examination
2 required in Section 6-187 of this title; and
3 5. A minimum of two (2) years of successful teaching experience
4 in public or private schools accredited by the State Board of
5 Education or by the proper accrediting authority of another state of
6 the United States.
7 C. The certification requirements for a superintendent of
8 schools not alternatively certified under subsection D of this
9 section shall include not less than:
10 1. Certification as a school principal or completion of the
11 certification requirements for a school principal as set forth in
12 subsection B of this section;
13 2. Completion of a program in education administration approved
14 by the Oklahoma Commission for Teacher Preparation Educational
15 Quality and Accountability with an emphasis on district-level
16 leadership skills, and which shall include the following
17 competencies:
18 a. instructional leadership,
19 b. organizational leadership, including education
20 finance, education law, and risk management,
21 c. collaborative and community leadership, and
22 d. ethical leadership.
23 The requirement in this paragraph shall not apply to any person
24 who has completed an Oklahoma a Commission for Teacher Preparation
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1594 SFLR Page 4
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 Educ ational Quality and Accountability approved Master’s Degree in
2 Education Administration master’s degree in education administration
3 or has completed a program in education that included competencies
4 that are substantially equal to those listed in this paragraph, and
5 if the degree or program was completed between the effective date of
6 this act and July 1, 2005;
7 3. Any other professional education and requirements as may be
8 fixed by the State Board of Education;
9 4. A passing score on the subject area competency examination
10 required in Section 6-187 of this title; and
11 5. A minimum of two (2) years of administrative experience in
12 public or private schools accredited by the State Board of Education
13 or by the proper accrediting authority of another state of the
14 United States.
15 D. 1. The standards for alternative certification for
16 superintendents of schools and principals shall include:
17 a. the completion of a standard master’s degree,
18 b. two (2) years of relevant work experience in a
19 supervisory or administrative capacity,
20 c. a passing score on the subject area competency
21 examination required in Section 6-187 of this title,
22 and
23 d. filing with the director of teacher education at an
24 Oklahoma accredited institution of higher education a
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1594 SFLR Page 5
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 plan for completing an alternative administrative
2 preparation program within three (3) years. Relevant
3 work experience and coursework may be considered and
4 applied to complete the plan.
5 2. An alternative certificate for superintendent of schools and
6 principals shall not exceed three (3) years and shall not be
7 renewable.
8 3. Upon successful completion of an alternative administrative
9 preparation program by a participant, the State Board of Education
10 shall issue a standard certificate for superintendent or principal,
11 as applicable, to the applicant.
12 4. Any person participating in an alternative certification
13 program for superintendent of schools and principals on the
14 effective date of this act July 1, 2005, shall be subject to the
15 program requirements in effect prior to the effective date of this
16 act July 1, 2005.
17 E. The certification requirements for a superintendent of a
18 technology center school district shall include not less than a
19 standard master’s degree, any other professional education
20 requirements as may be fixed by the State Board of Education, and a
21 minimum of four (4) years teaching, supervisory, or administrative
22 experience, which may include teaching of full-time adult students,
23 in a technology center school district. A person meeting the
24 requirements set forth in subsection C of this section shall be
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1594 SFLR Page 6
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 elig ible for a certificate for superintendent of a technology center
2 school district.
3 F. The State Board of Career and Technology Education shall
4 promulgate rules for a certification system specifically for
5 teachers and instructors in the technology center school districts.
6 The system shall be competency-based. The competencies for
7 certification shall include industry-based skills, standards, and
8 certifications.
9 G. Certificates issued by the State Board of Education may be
10 revoked by the State Board of Education for willful violation of any
11 rule of the Board or of any federal or state law or other proper
12 cause but only after sufficient hearing has been given before the
13 Board.
14 H. Teaching in a Head Start program or programs shall be used
15 for renewal of a standard teaching certificate.
16 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
17 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
18 of the public peace, health, or safety, an emergency is hereby
19 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
20 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
